 def checkXMatrix(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> bool:\n        n = len(grid)\n        for i in range(n):\n            for j in range(n):\n                if i == j or i + j == n - 1:\n                    if grid[i][j] == 0:\n                        return False\n                else:\n                    if grid[i][j] != 0:\n                        return False\n        return True\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through each element of the grid and checks the conditions for an X-Matrix:\n\n1. If the element is on one of the diagonals (i.e., `i == j` or `i + j == n - 1`), it should be non-zero.\n2. If the element is not on one of the diagonals, it should be zero.\n\nIf any of these conditions are violated, the function returns `False`. If the loop completes without finding any violations, the function returns `True`.", "estimated_date": 1656201600000}